---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="DFOS Protocol"
  description="Cryptographic identity and verifiable authorship for private spaces. Ed25519 signed chains, content-addressed proofs, W3C DIDs. MIT License."
  landing={true}
>
  <!-- ═══ Hero ═══ -->
  <section class="hero">
    <header class="site-header site-header--landing">
      <a href="/" class="logo">
        <img src="/dfos-logo-green.svg" alt="DFOS" />
      </a>
      <nav>
        <a href="/overview">Why</a>
        <a href="/spec">Spec</a>
        <a href="/did-method">DID</a>
        <a href="/content-model">Content</a>
        <a href="/credentials">Credentials</a>
        <a href="/web-relay">Relay</a>
        <a href="/cli">CLI</a>
        <a href="/deploy">Deploy</a>
        <a href="/faq">FAQ</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/metalabel/dfos">GitHub</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <div class="hero-overlay">
      <p class="hero-declaration" id="hero-typed">
        YOUR IDENTITY AND CONTENT ARE RENTED BACK TO YOU BY THE PLATFORMS THAT OWN IT. <span class="green">DFOS PROTOCOL GIVES YOU BACK THE KEYS.</span>
      </p>
      <p class="hero-pitch">
        An open standard for cryptographic identity and verifiable content. Runs anywhere, portable across everything, no permission required.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="hero-below">
      <h1 class="hero-headline">
        The proof is public. The content is private
      </h1>
      <div class="hero-cta">
        <a href="#get-started" class="hero-cta-link">Install the CLI</a>
        <a href="/overview" class="hero-cta-link">Why this exists</a>
        <a href="/spec" class="hero-cta-link">Read the spec</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ Dark Forest ═══ -->
  <section class="two-worlds-section">
    <div class="two-worlds-inner">
      <div class="two-worlds-card" id="tilt-card">
        <img src="/card-hands.png" alt="" class="two-worlds-card-img" />
      </div>
      <div class="two-worlds-text">
        <span class="section-label">The Dark Forest</span>
        <h2>Two worlds</h2>
        <p>
          The most meaningful creative and social coordination on the internet
          happens in private groups, closed communities, invite-only spaces.
          The topology is private-first.
        </p>
        <p>
          Every existing system collapses proof and content into the same surface.
          If you can't access the content, you can't verify anything about it.
          DFOS separates them.
        </p>
        <p>
          The world of proofs is public &mdash; signed chains that anyone can verify.
          The world of content exists in dark forests &mdash; member-governed spaces,
          visible only to participants.
          The protocol defines the proof world. It sees hashes, never documents.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ How It Works ═══ -->
  <section class="dark-section">
    <div class="dark-section-inner">
      <span class="section-label">T H E &nbsp; P R O T O C O L</span>

      <div class="concepts-three">
        <div class="concept-card">
          <h2>Self-certifying identity</h2>
          <p>
            Identity is a chain of cryptographic operations you control.
            Your <a href="/did-method"><code>did:dfos</code></a> identifier derives from
            your genesis &mdash; self-certifying. Forks are valid. Convergence is deterministic.
            No consensus needed.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="concept-card">
          <h2>Offline verification</h2>
          <p>
            Verification is a pure function. Public key + signed chain = valid or invalid.
            Any Ed25519 library, any language. The chain carries everything needed.
            A proof exported today is verifiable by code that doesn't exist yet.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="concept-card">
          <h2>Trustless distribution</h2>
          <p>
            <a href="/web-relay">Web relays</a> independently verify every operation
            on ingestion. No trust between relays. No hierarchy.
            Topology is emergent. Three peering behaviors compose the network:
            gossip, read-through, and sync.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ Credibility + Routing ═══ -->
  <section class="landing-section">
    <div class="credibility-strip">
      <span>MIT License</span>
      <span class="credibility-dot">&middot;</span>
      <span>Powers the <a href="https://dfos.com">DFOS platform</a></span>
      <span class="credibility-dot">&middot;</span>
      <span>TypeScript &middot; Go &middot; Python &middot; Rust &middot; Swift</span>
    </div>
    <p class="credibility-sub">
      Same deterministic test vectors across all five implementations.
      <a href="/spec">The protocol specification</a> is the single source of truth.
    </p>

    <div class="intent-routing">
      <a href="#get-started" class="intent-card">
        <span class="intent-label">B U I L D</span>
        <span class="intent-title">Install the CLI</span>
        <span class="intent-desc">One binary. Create identities, sign content, run relays. Linux, macOS, Windows.</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/overview" class="intent-card">
        <span class="intent-label">U N D E R S T A N D</span>
        <span class="intent-title">Why this exists</span>
        <span class="intent-desc">The structural condition of platform identity, the dark forest topology, and what falls out of it.</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/spec" class="intent-card">
        <span class="intent-label">E V A L U A T E</span>
        <span class="intent-title">Read the spec</span>
        <span class="intent-desc">Chains, beacons, merkle trees, CID derivation, verification rules, and deterministic test vectors.</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ Key Separator ═══ -->
  <section class="key-separator">
    <img src="/key-icon-green.svg" alt="" class="key-separator-icon" />
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ Get Started ═══ -->
  <section class="landing-section get-started" id="get-started">
    <span class="section-label">G E T &nbsp; S T A R T E D</span>
    <h2>Install the CLI</h2>
    <p class="get-started-intro">
      One binary. Keys in your OS keychain. Local-first by default.
      <a href="/cli">Full documentation</a>.
    </p>

    <div class="install-primary">
      <div class="install-code">
        <code>curl -sSL https://protocol.dfos.com/install.sh | sh</code>
        <button class="install-copy" aria-label="Copy command">copy</button>
      </div>
      <p class="install-alt">
        Also available via
        <code>brew install metalabel/tap/dfos</code>
        and
        <code>docker pull ghcr.io/metalabel/dfos</code>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="quickstart-block">
      <div class="install-label">Quickstart</div>
      <pre class="quickstart-pre"><code set:html={`<span class="qs-comment"># create your identity</span>
dfos identity create --name myname

<span class="qs-comment"># publish your first post</span>
echo '{"body":"gm"}' | dfos content create -

<span class="qs-comment"># see it</span>
dfos content list

<span class="qs-comment"># run a relay</span>
dfos serve`} /></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ Specifications ═══ -->
  <section class="landing-section">
    <span class="section-label">S P E C I F I C A T I O N S</span>
    <h2>Read the protocol</h2>

    <div class="spec-links spec-links--quad">
      <a href="/spec" class="spec-link">
        <span class="spec-link-title">Protocol Specification</span>
        <span class="spec-link-desc">Chains, beacons, merkle trees, CID derivation, verification rules, test vectors</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/did-method" class="spec-link">
        <span class="spec-link-title">DID Method</span>
        <span class="spec-link-desc">W3C <code>did:dfos</code> &mdash; self-certifying, transport-agnostic identifiers</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/content-model" class="spec-link">
        <span class="spec-link-title">Content Model</span>
        <span class="spec-link-desc">JSON Schema content types committed via content-addressed CIDs</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/credentials" class="spec-link">
        <span class="spec-link-title">Credentials</span>
        <span class="spec-link-desc">Delegated authorization, revocation, standing access, and attenuation</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/web-relay" class="spec-link">
        <span class="spec-link-title">Web Relay</span>
        <span class="spec-link-desc">Verifying HTTP relay with gossip, read-through, and sync peering</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/siwd" class="spec-link">
        <span class="spec-link-title">Sign In With DFOS</span>
        <span class="spec-link-desc">Cryptographic identity verification for third-party applications</span>
      </a>
    </div>

    <span class="section-label" style="margin-top: 3rem;">U S E &nbsp; I T</span>

    <div class="spec-links">
      <a href="/cli" class="spec-link">
        <span class="spec-link-title">CLI</span>
        <span class="spec-link-desc">Identities, content chains, credentials, relays &mdash; Linux, macOS, Windows</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/deploy" class="spec-link">
        <span class="spec-link-title">Deploy</span>
        <span class="spec-link-desc">Run a relay with Docker, Caddy auto-TLS, peering, and container images</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/skill" class="spec-link">
        <span class="spec-link-title">Claude Code Skill</span>
        <span class="spec-link-desc">AI-assisted CLI workflows &mdash; install the DFOS skill for Claude Code</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/overview" class="spec-link">
        <span class="spec-link-title">Why</span>
        <span class="spec-link-desc">The structural condition, design principles, what the protocol is and isn't</span>
      </a>
    </div>

    <hr class="section-divider" />

    <ul class="resource-list">
      <li>
        <a href="/faq">FAQ</a>
        <span class="desc">&mdash; design decisions, AT Protocol comparison, blockchain identity</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://github.com/metalabel/dfos">GitHub</a>
        <span class="desc">&mdash; metalabel/dfos &mdash; MIT License</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://github.com/metalabel/dfos/releases/latest">Releases</a>
        <span class="desc">&mdash; pre-built binaries for all platforms</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/@metalabel/dfos-protocol">npm</a>
        <span class="desc">&mdash; TypeScript protocol library (see also: <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/@metalabel/dfos-web-relay">dfos-web-relay</a>)</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://schemas.dfos.com">schemas.dfos.com</a>
        <span class="desc">&mdash; JSON Schema definitions</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="/llms-full.txt">llms-full.txt</a>
        <span class="desc">&mdash; full protocol content as plain text</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <script is:inline>
    document.querySelectorAll('.install-copy').forEach(function (btn) {
      btn.addEventListener('click', function () {
        var code = btn.parentElement.querySelector('code').textContent;
        navigator.clipboard.writeText(code).then(function () {
          var prev = btn.textContent;
          btn.textContent = 'copied';
          setTimeout(function () { btn.textContent = prev; }, 1500);
        });
      });
    });

    // scroll-driven image brightness
    (function () {
      var targets = [];
      document.querySelectorAll('.split-image, .key-separator').forEach(function (el) {
        targets.push({ el: el, mode: 'contain' });
      });
      document.querySelectorAll('.closing-image').forEach(function (el) {
        targets.push({ el: el, mode: 'enter' });
      });
      targets = targets.filter(function (t) { return t.el; });

      function update() {
        var vh = window.innerHeight;
        targets.forEach(function (t) {
          var rect = t.el.getBoundingClientRect();
          var ratio;
          if (t.mode === 'enter') {
            var entered = vh - rect.top;
            ratio = Math.min(1, Math.max(0, entered / (rect.height * 0.5)));
          } else {
            var visibleTop = Math.max(0, rect.top);
            var visibleBottom = Math.min(vh, rect.bottom);
            var visibleHeight = Math.max(0, visibleBottom - visibleTop);
            var visibleRatio = visibleHeight / rect.height;
            ratio = Math.min(1, visibleRatio / 0.8);
          }
          ratio = ratio * ratio;
          t.el.style.setProperty('--scroll-brightness', ratio.toFixed(3));
        });
        requestAnimationFrame(update);
      }
      update();
    })();

    // 3D tilt card
    (function () {
      var card = document.getElementById('tilt-card');
      if (!card) return;
      card.addEventListener('mousemove', function (e) {
        var rect = card.getBoundingClientRect();
        var x = (e.clientX - rect.left) / rect.width;
        var y = (e.clientY - rect.top) / rect.height;
        var rotateY = (x - 0.5) * 20;
        var rotateX = (0.5 - y) * 20;
        card.style.transform = 'perspective(800px) rotateX(' + rotateX + 'deg) rotateY(' + rotateY + 'deg) scale(1.03)';
        card.style.boxShadow = '0 ' + (20 + rotateX * 2) + 'px 60px rgba(0,0,0,0.6)';
      });
      card.addEventListener('mouseleave', function () {
        card.style.transform = 'perspective(800px) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) scale(1)';
        card.style.boxShadow = '0 20px 60px rgba(0,0,0,0.5)';
      });
    })();

    // Mobile scroll tilt for card
    (function () {
      if (window.innerWidth > 768) return;
      var card = document.getElementById('tilt-card');
      if (!card) return;
      function update() {
        var rect = card.getBoundingClientRect();
        var vh = window.innerHeight;
        var center = (rect.top + rect.height / 2) / vh;
        var rotateX = (center - 0.5) * -18;
        var rotateY = Math.sin(center * 3) * 10;
        card.style.transform = 'perspective(800px) rotateX(' + rotateX + 'deg) rotateY(' + rotateY + 'deg)';
        requestAnimationFrame(update);
      }
      update();
    })();

    // Hero typewriter effect
    (function () {
      var el = document.getElementById('hero-typed');
      if (!el) return;
      var html = el.innerHTML;
      // Wrap each character in a span, preserving HTML tags
      var wrapped = '';
      var inTag = false;
      for (var i = 0; i < html.length; i++) {
        var ch = html[i];
        if (ch === '<') { inTag = true; wrapped += ch; continue; }
        if (ch === '>') { inTag = false; wrapped += ch; continue; }
        if (inTag) { wrapped += ch; continue; }
        if (ch === ' ') { wrapped += ' '; continue; }
        wrapped += '<span class="char">' + ch + '</span>';
      }
      el.innerHTML = wrapped;
      el.classList.add('typing');

      var chars = el.querySelectorAll('.char');
      var delay = 800; // wait for painting fade-in
      var speed = 25;  // ms per character
      for (var j = 0; j < chars.length; j++) {
        (function (c, t) {
          setTimeout(function () { c.classList.add('visible'); }, t);
        })(chars[j], delay + j * speed);
      }
    })();
  </script>

  <!-- ═══ Closing ═══ -->
  <footer class="closing">
    <div class="closing-image">
      <img src="/painting-angel.jpg" alt="" />
    </div>
    <div class="closing-content">
      <img src="/key-icon-green.svg" alt="" class="closing-key" />
      <div class="closing-mark">DFOS Protocol</div>
      <nav class="closing-nav">
        <a href="/overview">Why</a>
        <a href="/spec">Spec</a>
        <a href="/did-method">DID</a>
        <a href="/content-model">Content</a>
        <a href="/credentials">Credentials</a>
        <a href="/web-relay">Relay</a>
        <a href="/cli">CLI</a>
        <a href="/deploy">Deploy</a>
        <a href="/skill">Skill</a>
        <a href="/faq">FAQ</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/metalabel/dfos">GitHub</a>
        <a href="https://dfos.com">dfos.com</a>
      </nav>
      <p class="closing-credits">Yancey &middot; Ilya &middot; Brandon &middot; Lena</p>
      <p class="closing-credits"><a href="https://github.com/metalabel/dfos/blob/main/LICENSE">MIT License</a> &middot; 2026</p>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Base>
